The International Rescue Committee (IRC) responds to the world’s worst humanitarian crises and helps people to survive and rebuild their lives. Founded in 1933 at the request of Albert Einstein, the IRC offers lifesaving care and life-changing assistance to refugees forced to flee from war or disaster. At work today in over 40 countries and 22 U.S. cities, we restore safety, dignity and hope to millions who are uprooted and struggling to endure. The IRC leads the way from harm to home. We are recruiting to fill the position of: Requisition ID: req10422Location: Maiduguri, BornoSector: Emergency ResponseEmployment Category: RegularEmployment Type: Full-TimeOpen to Expatriates: No Job Overview/Summary Major ResponsibilitiesProgram development: Program Implementation: Planning and Budget Management: Human Resource and Administration: Partner Management: Program Monitoring, Evaluation, and Reporting: Coordination and Representation: Other Duties: Key Working Relationships: Qualifications Work Experience: Demonstrated Skills and Competencies: Language Skills: Application Closing DateNot Specified. The post Economic Recovery and Development Senior Manager at the International Rescue Committee (IRC) appeared first on Jobs in Nigeria – http://jobsinnigeria.careers. Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.